<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 6:25AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>......Light snow and poor driving visibility will impact portions of
North Central MT through 745 AM MST...
At 620 AM MST, light snow was falling across much of North
Central MT.
HAZARD...Poor driving visibility because of falling snow and passing
vehicles. New snow accumulations less than a quarter of a
inch.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Passing vehicles are creating clouds of snow, making
passing vehicles difficult.
Locations impacted include...
Much of North Central MT south of Highway 2.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 from Sieben flats to Conrad.
Highway 200 from Rogers Pass to Lewistown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Use caution while driving because of poor visibility.</instruction>
